Nqaba Charles convicted of killing Constable Devin Hattingh on July 28, 2014 Picture: Kathryn Kimberley Charles Nqaba, 26, convicted of murdering Constable Devin Hattingh in 2014, was sentenced to an effective 18 years in prison in the Port Elizabeth High Court on Wednesday. The deceased&#8217;s father John Hattingh said he was disappointed with the sentence. &#8220;He can still be released in a few years, but my son will never come back,&#8221; Hattingh said after proceedings. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share